; prototype-merge.form — keep the interned prototype set lean: flag the redundant exemplar before it bloats.
;
; THE ASK:
;   nearest-shape.fk GROWS a prototype set — interning a new exemplar is the smallest act of learning,
;   adding without forgetting. That is the right move for learning and the wrong move forever: a set
;   that only ever grows accumulates duplicates. Intern "dog" [9 1 0 7] today and "dog" [9 1 0 6]
;   tomorrow and the recognizer carries two cells that route the same query to the same label — twice
;   the walk, no extra discrimination. This is the complementary breath to nearest-shape: not how the
;   set GROWS, but when two of its cells have become the SAME cell and one can be released. The flag
;   is body, executable from the kernel; the policy of how lean to keep the set is DATA (a floor).
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable: form-stdlib/prototype-merge.fk · proven: tests/prototype-merge-band.fk -> 127)
;
;   A prototype = (list label vector), exactly the cell nearest-shape interns. A FLOOR = the minimum
;   agreeing-bin count that counts as "similar enough", supplied by the caller.
;
;   1. ACCESSORS  pm-label / pm-vec: read the label and the feature-vector off a prototype — the same
;      (label, vector) shape the recognizer holds, so a cell flagged here is the cell routed there.
;   2. SIMILARITY  pm-sim / pm-sim-walk: walk the two vectors in LOCKSTEP and COUNT the positions that
;      agree. The same content-addressing count nearest-shape uses — but INLINED, owing nothing to a
;      sibling recipe (a stdlib recipe never calls another's functions; the lockstep walk is small
;      enough to carry its own). No subtraction, no distance, no float: how many bins match.
;   3. REDUNDANT?  pm-redundant?: two prototypes are a duplicate when they SAY the same thing (same
;      label, by str_eq) AND SENSE the same way (agreement ge the floor). Both halves required; the
;      result is a 1/0 flag — settle the returned (and …) to a bit with (if … 1 0), the and-binary
;      discipline, never let a raw (and …) escape as the value.
;
; WHY BOTH HALVES OF THE GATE:
;   label-match alone is not enough: two same-label cells can be a coarse exemplar and a fine one of
;   one shape (a sharp [9 1 0 7] and a faint [9 0 0 0]) — two honest dialects of "dog", both worth
;   keeping. similarity alone is not enough either: an IDENTICAL vector under a DIFFERENT label is a
;   real collision of two shapes ([9 1 0 7] as both "dog" and "cat") — keep both, a merge there would
;   erase a shape. Only same-label-AND-similar-enough is the provable duplicate that earns the flag.
;
; WHY FORM-NATIVE / CONTENT-ADDRESSED:
;   a prototype is a substrate cell; its Blueprint NodeID IS its vector's structure, identical on every
;   kernel. "These two cells are redundant" is therefore the SAME verdict on Go, Rust, and TS — the
;   validate.sh three-way parity is dedup parity, not a hope that three runtimes agree on a heuristic.
;   The set the Mac prunes is the set the phone prunes, the lean cell-set verifiable by NodeID. Pruning
;   is a predicate over pairs, not new control flow; the flag never depends on which prototypes exist,
;   only on their labels and vectors.
;
; HONEST LANE / CAVEAT:
;   redundancy is exact-bin agreement gated by a count floor (inclusive — the gate is ge, so agreement
;   EQUAL to the floor is redundant, agreement one below it is kept). It is NOT semantic equivalence.
;   Two vectors that mean the same shape but quantized into different bins — a coarse fingerprint and a
;   fine one — score below the floor and are KEPT as distinct. The flag is conservative by design: it
;   merges only provable duplicates and never collapses a shape it cannot prove identical. False-keep
;   (an unflagged near-duplicate) is the safe failure; false-merge (erasing a real shape) is the one it
;   refuses. Quantize first so the bins are honest, then dedup — the recipe makes no smoothness claim.
;
; KIN — the complementary breath of the recognizer and its neighbors:
;   nearest-shape.form (GROWS the set — interning is the smallest learning; this PRUNES it — the
;   smallest forgetting) · turboquant-as-recipe.form (the data-oblivious quantization that makes the
;   "bins" honest before either grow or prune) · novelty.form / drift-detect.form (when a reading is
;   new enough to intern vs. close enough to fold) · the three-way validate.sh (no trusted prover —
;   parallel kernels, what survives the agreement IS the dedup verdict).
